Description: Fragment of oval handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay coarse red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and symbol. Stamp not wholly impressed.
Type series: KT2466 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.51, 11. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0345)
